Cell.Data: If lymph nodes are present consider recording G2.20 (laterality & site(s) and numbers of lymph nodes)
If the histological tumour type is other, then record the other type.
If the histological tumour type is Adenocarcinoma (Acinar variant eg foamy, pseudohyperplastic), then record the variant.
If there are other nodules >10mm in diameter then record the locations in quadrant and plane.
If an extraprostatic extension is present, then record the extent and consider recording the locations(s) of the EPE.
If the location of the extraprostatic extension is other, then record the record the other locations(s) of the EPE.
If the margin status is involved, the record the location(s) and optionally the extent; the Gleason score at the margin and the type of positivity.
If the seminal vesicles are involved, then record the side.
If lymph nodes are present record S3.07 lymph node status.
If there are positive lymph nodes consider recording G3.09 laterality and G3.10 maximum dimension of largest deposit.
If there are positive lymph nodes with indicated laterality consider recording the site(s) of the involved nodes.
